  "texts": [
    "As the number of layers increases, the computational time also increases.",
    "When the indices are precomputed, the time gradually increases from 0.0078 s for one layer to 0.026 s for three layers.",
    "However, without precomputed indices, the time increases markedly, from 0.0391 s for one layer to 0.1291 s for three layers.",
    "These timings are important for both the training and inference phases.",
    "Although the computation of the sampling index is timeconsuming, the training time can be minimized by precomputing the indices as part of the data preprocessing step."
  ],
